
BUGS


[localtime]

- Localtime is wrong on the running safe-crux because never was
configured from system initialization script: /etc/rc

bash-4.2# date
Mon Mar 12 02:17:16 UTC 2012
bash-4.2# exit
exit
+ Unmounting target /dev/hda1 ...
/dev/hda1 has been unmounted
sepen@barebone:~/devel/crux/tools/safe-crux $ date
Mon Mar 12 03:17:18 CET 2012

- To fix that we can just do something like:

one:~/devel/crux/tools/safe-crux $ sudo rm -vf mnt/hda1/etc/localtime
removed `mnt/hda1/etc/localtime'
sepen@barebone:~/devel/crux/tools/safe-crux $ sudo cp -av /etc/localtime mnt/hda1/etc/
`/etc/localtime' -> `mnt/hda1/etc/localtime'
sepen@barebone:~/devel/crux/tools/safe-crux $ sudo ls -la mnt/hda1/etc/localtime
lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root 33 Mar 11 19:15 mnt/hda1/etc/localtime -> /usr/share/zoneinfo/Europe/Madrid
